{"word":"G5463 - χαίρω - chaírō - khah'-ee-ro - Farewell","slug":"G5463","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">χαίρω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>chaírō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>khah'-ee-ro"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Farewell"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03C7;&#x03B1;&#x03B9;&#x0301;&#x03C1;&#x03C9; - chairo&#x0304;</b> - <i>khah'ee-ro</i><p/>A primary verb; to be full of <i>&ldquo;cheer&rdquo;</i>, that is, calmly <i>happy</i> or well off; impersonal especially as a salutation (on meeting or parting), <i>be well:</i> - farewell, be glad, God speed, greeting, hail, joy (-fully), rejoice."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G2168\">G2168</a>, <a href=\"#/G2169\">G2169</a>, <a href=\"#/G2170\">G2170</a>, <a href=\"#/G4796\">G4796</a>, <a href=\"#/G5479\">G5479</a>, <a href=\"#/G5483\">G5483</a>, <a href=\"#/G5484\">G5484</a>, <a href=\"#/G5485\">G5485</a>, <a href=\"#/G5486\">G5486</a>, <a href=\"#/G5487\">G5487</a>, <a href=\"#/G884\">G884</a>"}]}